# ğŸŸ¢ PART-1 : LINUX (DEBIAN) â€“ VPN SERVER

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 1: Debian VM login karo

Terminal open karo
User: `shuhari` (ya jo bhi hai)

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 2: OpenVPN install karo (SERVER PE)

ğŸ‘‰ **Ye command Debian TERMINAL me hi likhni hai**

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openvpn easy-rsa -y
```

âœ”ï¸ Agar error nahi aaya â†’ OK

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 3: Easy-RSA folder banao

```bash
make-cadir ~/openvpn-ca
cd ~/openvpn-ca
```

ğŸ‘‰ Ab tum **openvpn-ca folder ke andar** ho

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 4: PKI initialize karo (certificate system)

```bash
./easyrsa init-pki
```

Output aaye:

```
init-pki complete
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 5: CA (Certificate Authority) banao

```bash
./easyrsa build-ca
```

### Jab puche:

```
Enter New CA Key Passphrase:
```

ğŸ‘‰ simple password daal do (example: `1234`)

```
Common Name:
```

ğŸ‘‰ likho:

```
VPN-CA
```

âœ”ï¸ CA ban gaya

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 6: Server certificate banao

```bash
./easyrsa build-server-full server nopass
```

âœ”ï¸ Server cert ready

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 7: Client certificate banao

```bash
./easyrsa build-client-full client1 nopass
```

âœ”ï¸ Client cert ready

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 8: Encryption key banao

```bash
openvpn --genkey --secret ta.key
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 9: OpenVPN server config file banao

```bash
sudo nano /etc/openvpn/server.conf
```

### Ye **POORA paste karo** ğŸ‘‡

```conf
port 1194
proto udp
dev tun

ca ca.crt
cert server.crt
key server.key
dh dh.pem
tls-auth ta.key 0

server 10.8.0.0 255.255.255.0
keepalive 10 120

persist-key
persist-tun

status openvpn-status.log
verb 3
```

Save â†’ `CTRL+O` â†’ Enter
Exit â†’ `CTRL+X`

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 10: Certificates copy karo OpenVPN folder me

```bash
sudo cp pki/ca.crt pki/issued/server.crt pki/private/server.key pki/dh.pem ta.key /etc/openvpn/
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 11: IP Forwarding ON karo

```bash
sudo nano /etc/sysctl.conf
```

Is line ko uncomment karo:

```conf
net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
```

Apply:

```bash
sudo sysctl -p
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 12: OpenVPN start karo

```bash
sudo systemctl start openvpn@server
sudo systemctl enable openvpn@server
```

Check:

```bash
sudo systemctl status openvpn@server
```

ğŸŸ¢ **Active (running)** dikhna chahiye

---

# ğŸŸ¢ PART-2 : WINDOWS â€“ VPN CLIENT

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 13: Windows me OpenVPN install karo

ğŸ‘‰ Browser me open karo:

```
https://openvpn.net/community-downloads/
```

âœ”ï¸ Download â†’ Install â†’ Next â†’ Finish

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 14: Client config file banao (Windows)

### Desktop pe:

Right click â†’ New â†’ Text file
Naam rakho:

```
client1.ovpn
```

### Isme paste karo ğŸ‘‡

```conf
client
dev tun
proto udp
remote <DEBIAN_IP> 1194

ca ca.crt
cert client1.crt
key client1.key
tls-auth ta.key 1

persist-key
persist-tun
verb 3
```

ğŸ‘‰ `<DEBIAN_IP>` = Debian ka IP
(Check: `ip a`)

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 15: Certificates Windows me copy karo

### Debian terminal me:

```bash
mkdir ~/client-files
cp pki/ca.crt pki/issued/client1.crt pki/private/client1.key ta.key ~/client-files/
```

ğŸ‘‰ Ye files **Windows ke OpenVPN config folder** me daalni hai:

```
C:\Program Files\OpenVPN\config\
```

âœ”ï¸ `client1.ovpn` bhi yahi rakho

---

## ğŸ”¹ STEP 16: VPN connect karo (Windows)

* System tray me OpenVPN icon
* Right click â†’ **Connect**
